title: Extract Tox Info from Various Databases
text: extractox comprehensive R package designed simplify querying various chemical, toxicological, biological databases Comparative Toxicogenomics Database (CTP) MDI Biological Laboratory NC State University, Integrated Chemical Environment (ICE) National Toxicology Program (NTP), Integrated Risk Information System (IRIS) Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), CompTox Chemicals Dashboard Resource Hub (CompTox) EPA, PubChem National Center Biotechnology Information/National Institures Health (NCBI, NIH). package facilitates interaction APIs, providing curated user-friendly outputs. communicate Pubchem, extractox relies packagewebchem.

title: Extract Tox Info from Various Databases
text: ICE database, managed EPA, provides access variety data related chemical toxicity, exposure, risk assessment. includes data high-throughput screening assays, vivo studies, computational models. extr_ice provides access NTP’s ICE database toxicological exposure-related data. 2000 possible assays ICE. extr_ice_assay_names() function allows search assay names match pattern ’re interested . Please note searches case sensitive accept regexp.
code: library(extractox) ice_data <- extr_ice(casrn = c("50-00-0"), assays = NULL) # assays is null so all assays are retrieved #> ℹ Checking Internet Connection... #> ℹ Internet connection OK... #> ℹ Sending request to ICE database... #> ℹ Request succeeded with status code: 200 names(ice_data) #>  [1] "assay"              "endpoint"           "substanceType"      #>  [4] "casrn"              "qsarReadyId"        "value"              #>  [7] "unit"               "species"            "receptorSpecies"    #> [10] "route"              "sex"                "strain"             #> [13] "lifeStage"          "tissue"             "lesion"             #> [16] "location"           "assaySource"        "inVitroAssayFormat" #> [19] "reference"          "referenceUrl"       "dtxsid"             #> [22] "substanceName"      "pubMedId" extr_ice_assay_names("Rat Acute") # keep empty to retrieve all #> [1] "Rat Acute Oral Toxicity"         "Rat Acute Inhalation Toxicity"   #> [3] "Rat Acute Dermal Toxicity"       "CATMoS, Rat Acute Oral Toxicity"

text: CTP provides information interactions chemicals, genes, diseases. helps understanding effects environmental exposures human health. series functions interact CTP database. extr_ctd extracts information related chemical-gene pathway associations. Tetramers computationally generated information units interrelate four data types CTP: chemical, gene product, phenotype, disease. help understanding complex relationships entities combined impact human health. extr_tetramer extract info related tetramers CTD.
code: input_terms <- c("50-00-0", "64-17-5", "methanal", "ethanol") ctd_association <- extr_ctd(   input_terms = input_terms,   category = "chem",   report_type = "genes_curated",   input_term_search_type = "directAssociations",   action_types = "ANY",   ontology = c("go_bp", "go_cc") ) #> ℹ Checking Internet Connection... #> ℹ Internet connection OK... #> ℹ Sending request to CTD database... #> ℹ Request succeeded with status code: 200   # Get expresssion data ctd_expression <- extr_ctd(   input_terms = input_terms,   report_type = "cgixns",   category = "chem",   action_types = "expression" ) #> ℹ Checking Internet Connection... #> ℹ Internet connection OK... #> ℹ Sending request to CTD database... #> ℹ Request succeeded with status code: 200  names(ctd_expression) #>  [1] "x_input"             "chemical_name"       "chemical_id"         #>  [4] "cas_rn"              "gene_symbol"         "gene_id"             #>  [7] "organism"            "organism_id"         "interaction"         #> [10] "interaction_actions" "pub_med_i_ds" tetramer_data <- extr_tetramer(   chem = c("50-00-0", "ethanol"),   disease = "",   gene = "",   go = "",   input_term_search_type = "directAssociations",   qt_match_type = "equals" ) #> ℹ Checking Internet Connection... #> ℹ Internet connection OK... #> ℹ Sending request to CTD database for tetramer data for 50-00-0... #> ℹ Request succeeded with status code: 200 #> ℹ Sending request to CTD database for tetramer data for ethanol... #> ℹ Request succeeded with status code: 200  names(tetramer_data) #> [1] "query"        "chemical"     "chemical_id"  "gene"         "gene_id"      #> [6] "phenotype"    "phenotype_id" "disease"      "disease_id"

title: Download and Extract Data from CompTox Chemistry Dashboard — extr_comptox
text: ids character vector containing items searched within CompTox Chemistry Dashboard. can chemical names, CAS Registry Numbers (CASRN), InChIKeys, DSSTox substance identifiers (DTXSID). download_items character vector items downloaded. includes comprehensive set chemical properties, identifiers, predictive data, relevant information. Default, download info CASRN Chemical Abstracts Service Registry Number, unique numerical identifier chemical substances. INCHIKEY hashed version full International Chemical Identifier (InChI) string. IUPAC_NAME International Union Pure Applied Chemistry (IUPAC) name chemical. SMILES Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System (SMILES) representation chemical structure. INCHI_STRING full International Chemical Identifier (InChI) string. MS_READY_SMILES SMILES representation chemical structure, prepared mass spectrometry analysis. QSAR_READY_SMILES SMILES representation chemical structure, prepared quantitative structure-activity relationship (QSAR) modeling. MOLECULAR_FORMULA chemical formula representing number type atoms molecule. AVERAGE_MASS average mass molecule, calculated based isotopic distribution elements. MONOISOTOPIC_MASS mass molecule calculated using abundant isotope element. QC_LEVEL quality control level data. SAFETY_DATA Safety information related chemical. EXPOCAST Exposure predictions EPA's ExpoCast program. DATA_SOURCES Sources data provided. TOXVAL_DATA Toxicological values related chemical. NUMBER_OF_PUBMED_ARTICLES number articles related chemical PubMed. PUBCHEM_DATA_SOURCES Sources data PubChem. CPDAT_COUNT number entries Chemical Product Categories Database (CPDat). IRIS_LINK Link EPA's Integrated Risk Information System (IRIS) entry chemical. PPRTV_LINK Link EPA's Provisional Peer-Reviewed Toxicity Values (PPRTV) entry chemical. WIKIPEDIA_ARTICLE Link Wikipedia article chemical. QC_NOTES Notes related quality control data. ABSTRACT_SHIFTER Information related abstract shifter. TOXPRINT_FINGERPRINT ToxPrint chemoinformatics fingerprint chemical. ACTOR_REPORT Aggregated Computational Toxicology Resource (ACTOR) report chemical. SYNONYM_IDENTIFIER Identifiers synonyms chemical. RELATED_RELATIONSHIP Information related chemicals. ASSOCIATED_TOXCAST_ASSAYS Assays associated chemical ToxCast database. TOXVAL_DETAILS Details toxicological values. CHEMICAL_PROPERTIES_DETAILS Details chemical properties. BIOCONCENTRATION_FACTOR_TEST_PRED Predicted bioconcentration factor tests. title: Extract Data from the CTD API — extr_ctd
text: function queries Comparative Toxicogenomics Database API retrieve data related chemicals, diseases, genes, categories.

title: Extract Data from the CTD API — extr_ctd
code: extr_ctd(   input_terms,   category = "chem",   report_type = "genes_curated",   input_term_search_type = "directAssociations",   action_types = NULL,   ontology = NULL,   verify_ssl = FALSE,   verbose = TRUE,   ... )

title: Extract Data from the CTD API — extr_ctd
text: input_terms character vector input terms CAS numbers IUPAC names. category string specifying category data query. Valid options "", "chem", "disease", "gene", "go", "pathway", "reference", "taxon". Default "chem". report_type string specifying type report return. Default "genes_curated". Valid options include: "cgixns" Curated chemical-gene interactions. Requires least one action_types parameter. "chems" chemical associations. "chems_curated" Curated chemical associations. "chems_inferred" Inferred chemical associations. "genes" gene associations. "genes_curated" Curated gene associations. "genes_inferred" Inferred gene associations. "diseases" disease associations. "diseases_curated" Curated disease associations. "diseases_inferred" Inferred disease associations. "pathways_curated" Curated pathway associations. "pathways_inferred" Inferred pathway associations. "pathways_enriched" Enriched pathway associations. "phenotypes_curated" Curated phenotype associations. "phenotypes_inferred" Inferred phenotype associations. "go" Gene Ontology (GO) associations. Requires least one ontology parameter. "go_enriched" Enriched GO associations. Requires least one ontology parameter. input_term_search_type string specifying search method use. Options "hierarchicalAssociations" "directAssociations". Default "directAssociations". action_types optional character vector specifying one interaction types filtering results. Default "". acceptable inputs "abundance", "activity", "binding", "cotreatment", "expression", "folding", "localization", "metabolic processing"...See https://ctdbase.org/tools/batchQuery.go full list. ontology optional character vector specifying one ontologies filtering GO reports. Default NULL. verify_ssl Boolean control SSL verified . verbose logical value indicating whether print detailed messages. Default TRUE. ... arguments supplied req_option thus libcurl.

what: Retrieve WHO IARC Monograph Information — extr_monograph
title: Retrieve WHO IARC Monograph Information — extr_monograph
text: function retrieves information regarding Monographs World Health Organization () International Agency Research Cancer (IARC)  based CAS Registry Number Name chemical.

title: Retrieve WHO IARC Monograph Information — extr_monograph
code: extr_monograph(ids, search_type = "casrn", verbose = TRUE)

title: Retrieve WHO IARC Monograph Information — extr_monograph
text: ids character vector IDs search . search_type character string specifying type search perform. Valid options "cas_rn" (CAS Registry Number) "name" (name chemical). search_type "casrn", function filters CAS Registry Number. search_type "name", function performs partial match search chemical name. verbose logical value indicating whether print detailed messages. Default TRUE.

title: Extract Tetramer Data from the CTD API — extr_tetramer
text: chem string indicating chemical identifiers CAS number IUPAC name chemical. disease string indicating disease term. Default empty string. gene string indicating gene symbol. Default empty string. go string indicating Gene Ontology term. Default empty string. input_term_search_type string specifying search method use. Options "hierarchicalAssociations" "directAssociations". Default "directAssociations". qt_match_type string specifying query type match method. Options "equals" "contains". Default "equals". verify_ssl Boolean control SSL verified . Default FALSE. verbose logical value indicating whether print detailed messages. Default TRUE. ... arguments supplied req_option thus libcurl.

what: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
title: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
text: wrapper function retrieves toxicological information specified chemicals calling several external functions query multiple databases, including PubChem, Integrated Chemical Environment (ICE), CompTox Chemicals Dashboard, Integrated Risk Information System (IRIS).

title: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
code: extr_tox(casrn, verbose = TRUE)

title: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
text: casrn character vector CAS Registry Numbers (CASRN) representing chemicals interest. verbose logical value indicating whether print detailed messages. Default TRUE.

title: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
text: list data frames containing toxicological information retrieved database: who_iarc_monographs Lists , IARC monographs related chemical. ghs_dat Toxicity data PubChem's Globally Harmonized System (GHS) classification. ice_dat Assay data Integrated Chemical Environment (ICE) database. iris Risk assessment data IRIS database. iris Risk assessment data IRIS database. comptox_list List dataframe toxicity information CompTox Chemicals Dashboard.

title: Extract Toxicological Information from Multiple Databases — extr_tox
text: Specifically, function: Calls extr_monograph return monographs informations IARC. Calls extr_pubchem_ghs retrieve GHS classification data PubChem. Calls extr_ice gather assay data ICE database. Calls extr_iris retrieve risk assessment information IRIS database. Calls extr_comptox retrieve data CompTox Chemicals Dashboard.
